```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return lowercase(strip(col)) |> replace => '-' => '_'
end
```

This function uses `lowercase` to convert the column name to lowercase, `strip` to remove leading and trailing whitespaces, and then a custom reduction with `replace` to replace hyphens with underscores. The pipe operator (`|>`) is used to chain these operations together.

To test this function:

```julia
using Test

@testset "clean_column" begin
    @test clean_column("My Column") == "my_column"
    @test clean_column("my column") == "my_column"
    @test clean_column("my-column") == "my_column"
    @test clean_column("MY COLUMN") == "my_column"
    # Add more tests here as needed...
end
```

Remember to include the `Test` package at the top and use the `@testset` macro followed by a block of test cases. This ensures that your function works correctly for different input scenarios.
